Description: Fragment of round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine purplish brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Ellanikos. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0281.19.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0596)
